OFFICIAL-SENSITIVE
ATLAS - CRIME MANAGEMENT (CM) INTELLIGENCE REPORT
3x5x2 GRADED . IR (Intelligence Report)
IR / URN
	GMP/OG/IR/2026/0291

Originating Unit
	GMP Serious & Organised Crime - OP GANNET MIR

Reporting Officer
	DC 70219 PATEL (handler ref H/441)

Date / Time Reported
	08/06/2026 14:12

Protective Marking
	OFFICIAL-SENSITIVE - POLICE

3x5x2 Grading
	[2 A P] (Source 2 Untested . Intelligence A Confirmed . Handling P)

Sanitised
	YES - handler sanitised for dissemination

OCG / CG
	CG NORTHSIDE (OCG-GM-2291)

INTELLIGENCE
DARREN COLE (DOB 14/03/1987, PNCID 2005/0456231K) is the principal of the NORTHSIDE organised crime group and controls the importation and onward supply of Class A controlled drugs across Greater Manchester. COLE uses NORTHGATE LOGISTICS LTD (Co. No. 11428876) as a front to launder cash proceeds.
COLE contactable on 07700 900118. He uses a second handset 07700 900342 (IMEI 359872041256683) for criminal liaison. On 12/02/2026 COLE flew from Manchester to Malaga with Sofia DRAGOMIR to meet a Spanish supplier; the trip was booked under PNR K7T2QL. COLE drives a black Audi Q7, registration LD18 KPN.
LEE FOSTER (DOB 02/11/1991, PNCID 2010/0782145M) acts as transport and uses the white Ford Transit VK69 RNZ, registered to NORTHGATE LOGISTICS LTD, to move consignments. NADIA ANSARI (DOB 27/06/1994) launders cash through book-keeping for the front company and moves money via account 81226740. ANPR shows LD18 KPN and VK69 RNZ travelling in convoy on the M60 on 04/06/2026.
ANALYST / RISK
Assessment: COLE directs; FOSTER transports; ANSARI launders. Firearms access indicated (WEA marker on PNC). Cash deposits inconsistent with declared turnover - refer to SAR cross-ref and HMRC return.
DISSEMINATION
Handling Code
	P - may be disseminated to other law-enforcement

Conditions
	None

Review Date
	08/12/2026

