REASON FOR SUSPICION
[XX-CASH][XX-NEX] Over a six-week period (21/04/2026-02/06/2026) the personal account of Darren COLE (a/c 30021847) received 14 cash deposits totalling GBP 148,750, each below the GBP 10,000 reporting threshold, paid in at branches across Greater Manchester. Within 48 hours funds were transferred to the business account of NORTHGATE LOGISTICS LTD (a/c 40918256) and described as 'haulage invoices'. No corresponding trade activity is evident. On 27/05/2026 EUR 60,000 was sent by international transfer to a beneficiary in Malaga, Spain.
The cash turnover is wholly inconsistent with the customer's declared income. The bookkeeper, Nadia ANSARI, instructed several of the transfers. The reporter seeks a DAML (no consent) before processing a pending GBP 24,000 outbound payment.
